SUMMARY:Raindrops on Tin Roofs
DESCRIPTION:Eldo is afraid of the storm. But one night\, he steps outside anyway. \nIs darkness visible or invisible? What does it tell us about the world? These are the questions that led Athulya Pillai and Pankaj Singh to create Eldo: an illustrated story set in a forest by the sea. And these are the questions you are invited to explore together. \nThrough reading\, listening\, and drawing\, you will examine what darkness means. What does it reveal about how children and adults see the world differently\, and where do those views unexpectedly overlap? \n\nAround the World in 50 Sundays is a journey that begins\, not with a ticket\, but with opening a book. In a city like Bangalore where families are always in motion\, the BIC Library hopes to offer stillness and a quiet\, welcoming space for both parents and children where reading becomes a shared experience. \nEvery Sunday\, we open our doors to invite you into a library that listens; building a rhythm of return\, a habit of joy and a new community bound not just by books\, but by the weekly ritual of reading together. \nWe welcome your ideas and input. If you have suggestions for children’s events or activities that align with this vision\, we’d love to hear from you. Please reach out to us at library@bangaloreinternationalcentre.org \n\n\nSupported by:\n\n
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/raindrops-on-tin-roofs/
LOCATION:Bangalore International Centre\, 7\, 4th Main Road\, Domlur II Stage\, Bangalore\, Karnataka\, 560071\, India
CATEGORIES:Around the World in 50 Sundays,Children's Books
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/Thumbnail__ROTR.jpg
END:VEVENT
